	<h1 >Atbash Cipher </h1 >
	
	
	
	<script type = "text/javascript">
	function cipherCode(keyIn, keyOut, msg) {

    var result = "";

    var add = function(ch) { result += (keyIn.indexOf(ch)==-1) ? ch : keyOut[keyIn.indexOf(ch)]; }

    for (var i = 0; i < msg.length; i++) { add(msg[i]); }

    return result;

}

var alphabet = "ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz";
var cipher = "ZYXWVUTSRQPONMLKJIHGFEDCBAzyxwvutsrqponmlkjihgfedcba";


function encode(message) { cForm.message.value = cipherCode(alphabet, cipher, message); }

function decode(message) { cForm.message.value = cipherCode(cipher, alphabet, message); }

	</script>

	<div class = "p1">
	<p class = "big"> 
	Atbash is another type of substitution cipher which is used with a specific key,
	where the alphabet is reversed ( A = Z, B = Y etc.)
	<br>
	It was orginally used to encrypt the hebrew alphabet
	<br> However, the fact that the key is fixed - this cipher is very limited in terms of security
	applications.
	
	<h2><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atbash">More background info</a></h2>
	
	</p>
